"title": "5571: surgery",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5571: surgery",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The physical removal of part of the human body, either in response to severe illness or as a form of punishment.</p>\n<h2>Medical surgery</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek30:21\">EZK 30:21</a></p>\n<h2>Punitive surgery</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:12\">DEU 25:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:6-Judg1:7\">JDG 1:6–1:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:51\">1SA 17:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam31:9\">1SA 31:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam4:7\">2SA 4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam4:12\">2SA 4:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:7\">2KI 25:7</a></p>\n<h2>Ritual or cultural surgery</h2>\n<h3>Castration</h3>\n<p>The primary meaning of <code>eunuch'' in the OT is</code>court officer'' and need not always imply castration; similarly with the NT counterpart:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs20:18\">2KI 20:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth2:3\">EST 2:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa56:3\">ISA 56:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:12\">MAT 19:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:27\">ACT 8:27</a></p>\n<h3>Circumcision</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:10-Gen17:14\">GEN 17:10–17:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:25\">EXO 4:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:3\">LEV 12:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh5:8\">JOS 5:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:21\">LUK 2:21</a></p>\n<h3>Dismemberment</h3>\n<p>A solemn call to the nation to act:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:29\">JDG 19:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam11:7\">1SA 11:7</a></p>\n<h3>Ear piercing</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:5-Exod21:6\">EXO 21:5–21:6</a> <em>There may be a reference to this in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:6\">Ps 40:6</a>.</em></p>\n<h3>Pagan mutilation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:28\">LEV 19:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:1\">DEU 14:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:28\">1KI 18:28</a></p>\n<h3>Animal sacrifices</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:10\">GEN 15:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:17\">EXO 29:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:6\">LEV 1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:12\">LEV 1:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:9\">LEV 3:9</a></p>\n<h2>Miraculous surgery</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:21-Gen2:22\">GEN 2:21–2:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:50-Luke22:51\">LUK 22:50–22:51</a></p>\n<h2>Spiritual surgery</h2>\n<h3>Heart transplant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:26\">EZK 36:26</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Amputation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:29-Matt5:30\">MAT 5:29–5:30</a></strong> <em>Jesus Christ is using hyperbole (deliberate exaggeration) to stress the need at times for radical action.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:8-Matt18:9\">MAT 18:8–18:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:43-Mark9:47\">MRK 9:43–9:47</a></p>\n<h3>Grafting</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:17-Rom11:24\">ROM 11:17–11:24</a></p>\n<h3>Pruning</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa18:5\">ISA 18:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:1-John15:2\">JHN 15:1–15:2</a></p>\n<h3>Felling</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:33-Isa10:34\">ISA 10:33–10:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:9\">LUK 3:9</a></p>",
